      • getCollectibleNames

        public IONames getCollectibleNames()
        Description copied from interface: Collector
        This method should return a set of collectible names, that can be collected from this collector. These names will be used by task plan builder to cross validate parallelism between two task graphs.

        If Collector C of task graph TG1 collects variable "var1" and C's parallelism is n, If Receptor R of task graph TG2 is interested in receiving "var1", R's parallelism should be equal to n and, R should have the same distribution as C among the workers.

        Specified by:
        getCollectibleNames in interface Collector
        Returns:
        set of names of collectbles
